Greetings from Abhyuday IIT Bombay,


Abhyuday, the social body of IIT Bombay has launched its nationwide
competition Action Plan for this year with a vision to empower students
across the nation to participate in the process of development.

E2APlanE2 or E2Action PlanE2 Competition is a 
launch pad for social ideas and
projects. We have effectively directed past 3 versions of APlan
competition covering about 20 states with participation of 140+ teams
including almost 500 students from 150 colleges nationwide in
ActionPlan,2015.

This nationwide competition will take participating teams through multiple
stages, starting from identifying a specific problem through stakeholder
interaction, progressing to engage with stakeholders and organizations in
developing a solution on models, and validating those ideas in the society
for further improvement.

The Action Plans or solution models will be validated and nurtured through
the strong network of Mentors, partner NGOs and social organisations.

The competition offers unique opportunities to convert an idea into action
through implementation support and internship opportunities with field
expert.

    Top 5 eligible Action Plans based on profit model will be considered
   for acceleration programme by SINE, IIT Bombay through which top 2 teams
   will be selected for this programme with  seed fundings of 3 lakhs per
   company . And net worth of 12 lakhs including seed fundings, networking,
   mentoring  and training  opportunities.
    Top nonprofit models will be implemented by various NGOs like Rashtri
ya
   Saksharta Mission Sanstha.
    Participation certificate to the teams who qualify 1st round
   satisfactorily.
    Internship and mentorship opportunities


For more information about the competition, please visit:
